text: "Nutbush City Limits" is a 1973 song by Ike & Tina Turner and is the title track from their studio album of the same name. It went to number 1 in Austria, number 2 in Germany and Switzerland, number 4 in the United Kingdom, number 9 in South Africa and Spain, number 12 in the Netherlands, number 14 in Australia, number 18 in Ireland, number 19 in New Zealand and number 22 in the United States. It went to be covered by Bob Seger and Tina Turner herself in 1991. ==References== Category:1973 songs Category:Funk rock songs Category:Country rock songs Category:Ike & Tina Turner songs Category:Bob Seger songs Category:Tina Turner songs
